Y86-64

X86-64

Datapath

CPU storage unit or register and ALU Bus

16 Register

  1. %rax - Accumulator, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  2. %rcx - Counter register, used for loops and general-purpose tasks (64-bit)
  3. %rdx - Data register, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  4. %rbx - Base register, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  5. %rsp - Stack pointer, points to the top of the stack (64-bit)
  6. %rbp - Base pointer, points to the base of the stack (64-bit)
  7. %rsi - Source index, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  8. %rdi - Destination index, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  9. %r8 - %r14 - Extended register, general-purpose register (64-bit)
  10. F

Stack and Push Pop

  • %rsp = stack pointer register 4 top of stack
  • stack memory memory
  • stack address memory top of stack address bottom
    • top of stack stack address stack address 1 top of stack address 1 stack top of stack address 2 stack stack address address

Push

stack memory

push rA

  1. %rsp - 8 top of stack 1 byte address
  2. rA copy address momory %rsp

  1. Decode
    1. valA = R4 register push memory
    2. valB = R4 address %rsp top of stack
  2. Execute valE = (-8) + valB stack
  3. Memory M4[valE] = valA rA stack
  4. Write Back R4 = valE update stack pointer
  5. PC Update PC = valP

Pop

stack memory

pop rA

  1. address memory %rsp rA
  2. %rsp + 8 stack 1 byte

  1. Decode valA = R4 valB = R4 address %rsp top of stack 2 register
    1. pop address top of stack stack
    2. address top of stack
  2. Execute valE = 8 + valB pop stack (Pop)
  3. Memory valM = M8[valA] top of stack memory valM
  4. Write Back
    1. dstE R4 = valE address stack pop %rsp
    2. dstM R[rA] = valM pop memory valM valM register
  5. PC update PC = valP

Call and Return

Call

push the address of next instrution and jump to function

call D D = memory address

  1. Fetch valC memory address function call
  2. Decode register R4 valB r4 R$ = %rsp stack pointer
  3. Execute valE = (-8) + valB stack
  4. Memory M8[valE] = valP valP next instruction memory next instruction function call function next instruction
  5. Write Back R4 = valE top of stack valP stack
  6. PC update PC = valC address function next instruction

Return

pop the address of next instruction and jump to that address

ret

  1. Decode valA = R4 valB = R4 address %rsp top of stack 2 register
    1. pop address top of stack stack
    2. address top of stack
  2. Execute valE = 8 + valB pop stack (Pop)
  3. Memory valM = M8[valA] top of stack memory valM
  4. Write Back R4 = valE address stack pop %rsp
  5. PC update PC = valM next instruction
